-------> STEWARDSHIP (10 min)

In every fellowship gathering we will be spending 10 minutes discussing stewardship as it relates to time, money and health

Stewardship describes the job of taking care of something valuable that we have been entrusted with

the word originates in old english combining stig (house) and ward (guard or keeper)

Keeper of the house

Within a Christian context, stewardship describes the responsibility that we have as Christians to maintain and wisely use the gifts that God has given us

Todays stewardship topic relates to money, and specifically, the importance of avoiding sinful currency that steals our time

I'm going to keep it simple because it is quite simple

Money is a tool used by humans as a way to store their time

You spend time helping someone build a house, they pay you money as a way to exhcnage value back to you

That money is a representation of our time which we can then use to exchange with others for things that we need or want

The tool of money has 3 functions:

1) Store of value. A way for us to store and preserve our time for future use
2) Medium of exchange. A tool we can use to exchange with others
3) Unit of account. A way to measure value and assign prices to things

Fiat currency is a fraudulent, perverted type of money. 

Fiat means by decree. Fiat currency like $cad or $usd is forced onto people by government and is normal to many because its what we're born into

The reason fiat currency is fraudulent is because government can print it out of thin air which is a form of counterfeiting and theft

By creating a trillion dollars with the click of a button, the currency supply is beiong inflated and everyone using that currency is effectively being stolen from 

Do not steal is the 8th commandment. Theft is a sin and any currency that has theft baked into it is therefore a sinful currency

The stewardship lesson of today is very simple: Do not participate in a sinful monetary system and do not store your time in a currency that can be inflated

Doing so is poor stewardship and not only makes you an accessory to sin, but it squanders away your most precious God given resource which is time

We honour God by opting out of a sinful monetary system and saving our time in honest money called bitcoi which I will speak much more about in future fellowship sessions


